##InvQ Technical UI Style Guide

 This document defines the visual constraints for the InvQ React frontend to ensure consistency across all dashboard routes.

 1. Design Tokens (Tailwind Configuration)
 All components must use these custom tokens. Avoid hardcoding hex values. 

Colors
| Name      | Hex       | CSS Class          | Usage                        |
|      :--- | :---      | :---               | :---                         | 
| Primary   | `#083344` | `bg-brand-dark`    | Sidebars, Page Headers       | 
| Action    | `#22D3EE` | `bg-brand-action`  | Primary Buttons, Active Tabs | 
| Accent    | `#0E7490` | `text-brand-accent`| Secondary Buttons, Links     | 
| Mist      | `#CFFAFE` | `bg-brand-mist`    | Active state backgrounds     | 
| Surface   | `#F8FAFC` | `bg-ui-page`       | Main content area background |

  Typography 
      -  Headings: `font-sans` | `font-bold` | `text-slate-900`
      -  Body: `font-sans`     | `text-slate-700` 
      -  Monospace:`font-mono` (Use for SKUs, Order IDs, and Port 4000/5173 logs)

2. Iconography 
  We use `lucide-react`. Do not import icons from other libraries to keep the bundle size small.
     - Inventory: `<Package />` 
     - Sales Orders: `<Handshake />` 
     - Purchase Orders: `<ShoppingCart />` 
     - Alerts: `<BellAlert />`

 3. Inventory Status Logic (QA Standards) When mapping inventory data from the backend, use these status indicators: 
      - Healthy: `Current Qty > Reorder Point` -> Badge: Green 
      - Warning: `Current Qty` within 10% of `Reorder Point` -> Badge: Amber
      - Danger:  `Current Qty <= Reorder Point` -> Badge: Red (Trigger Alert) 

4. Component Standards 
    Buttons 
      - Primary: `bg-brand-action` with white text and hover: `bg-brand-accent`.
  	  - Secondary: Transparent with `border-brand-accent` and `text-brand-accent`. 

    Form Inputs 
      - Must include a `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-action` state. 
      - Must display a red error message if the backend returns a `400` or `500` status code.




InvQ Technical Stack & Dependencies

UI & Styling (Pending Implementation) 
To match the approved wireframes, the following libraries must be installed in the `/frontend` directory: 

1. Tailwind CSS (Styling) 
  Used for the Deep Primary Teal (#083344) and Cyan designs. 
    -Install: `npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer && npx tailwindcss init -p` 

 2. Lucide-React (Icons)
    Used for all dashboard and sidebar iconography. 
      -Install: `npm install lucide-react.`

Environment Setup 
  Ensure your `.env` file in the backend contains:
     - `MONGODB_URI`
     - `JWT_SECRET`
     - `PORT=4000`
